Create a database master key
Create a certificate (fails without created db master key)
Create a symmetric key (encrypted by cert.)
Open the symmetric key
(5th - Update Col1)

T-SQL:

CREATE MASTER KEY ENCRYPTION BY PASSWORD = 'Best_Password789)';

CREATE CERTIFICATE MyCertificate
WITH SUBJECT = 'My Encryption Certificate';

CREATE SYMMETRIC KEY MySymmetricKey
WITH ALGORITHM = AES_256
ENCRYPTION BY CERTIFICATE MyCertificate;

OPEN SYMMETRIC KEY MySymmetricKey
DECRYPTION BY CERTIFICATE MyCertificate;

UPDATE YourTable
SET Col1 = EncryptByKey(Key_GUID('MySymmetricKey'), Col1);
